A sequel to two of my favourite indie shooter games on the Play Store. This one shocked me with the addition of microtransactions albeit being less greedy than even the most generous free2play shooters on the Store. This one features playable AI companions that can get their own weapons and outfits with each character having one outfit that costs real money. Then there's the grindy elements we all know and love from today's free mobile games. You run around collecting scrap for weapons. üåüüåüüåü

The game is lawfully good, also got some gore like dismemberment would love if the game had a full series about this game, like stranded on a mindless city or apocalyptic desert where you can drive vehicles. I do recommend the Slaughter series.
